707000f-b.title: Brooklyn: Surf Ave. - 22nd St. W.
707000f-b.text:
(1)
2201-2223 Surf Ave., north side, between West 23rd and 22nd Streets.
No. 2223 is in the foreground. The center building was the temporary
branch office of the Brooklyn Borough Gas Cog, distinguished by its flag-
pole. This building was formerly known as ''Grand View''.
January 1924.
Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.
MAY BE REPRODUCED.
(2)
The same.
December 31, 1924.
Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.
MAY BE REPRODUCED7
(3)
A limited view.
December 31, 1924.
Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.
MAY BE REPRODUCED.
(4)
The same as No. 3, after the Coney Island fire. Note the des-
truction of the former ''Grand View''.
August 8, 1932.
P. L. Sperr.
NO REPRODUCTIONS.

706999f-a.title: Brooklyn: Surf Ave. - 22nd St. W.
706999f-a.text:
Surf Ave., south side, between West 22nd and 23rd Streets; showing re-
aults of a fire in 1932, at Coney Ialand.
August 6, 1932.
P. L. Sperr.
NO REPRODUCTIONS.

702650f-b.title: Brooklyn: 22nd Street (West) - Surf Avenue
702650f-b.text:
West 22nd Street, at and adjoining the S. E. corner of
Surf Avenue, showing several bungalows being demolished for the
improvement of the area. The view is from Surf Avenue.
January, 1924
Eugene L. Armbruster Collection
MAY BE REPRODUCED
(2)
The same site, years later, showing the Socony gasoline
station and garage and the upper floor of a residence which re-
placed the old bungalows.
September 17, 1939
P. L. Sperr
NO REPRODUCTIONS
